e to LensKit 0.14.x, but compatibility with exactly 0.14.4 is not demonstrated and ItemItem(feedback='implicit') may not match that exact version. 2) Fulfilled: uses exact filenames u.data, VideoGames.csv, UserTaggedArtists-timestamps.dat. 3) Partially/Not fulfilled: MovieLens parsing is correct; Amazon assumes a 4-column no-header CSV without robust handling; Last.FM uses tab separator and columns heuristically, but does not robustly enforce documented schema/header handling. 4) Fulfilled: converts to implicit interaction pairs before splitting/training. 5) Fulfilled: filters MovieLens and Amazon ratings > 3. 6) Fulfilled: treats Last.FM tagged artist events as implicit interactions. 7) Fulfilled: iterative 5-core filtering is implemented. 8) Fulfilled: duplicate user-item pairs removed in k-core filter. 9) Fulfilled: exactly 5 distinct seeds are defined and recorded. 10) Fulfilled: user-based random 80/20 holdout is implemented per seed. 11) Not fulfilled: users unable to support a valid split are not excluded/reported; current splitter can create empty train for users with 1 interaction. 12) Fulfilled: trains ALS, ItemKNN, and Pop. 13) Not fulfilled: hyperparameters are not standard/default; ALS and ItemKNN are manually customized. 14) Fulfilled: ALS uses ImplicitMF, which is appropriate for implicit feedback. 15) Fulfilled: generates top-N recommendations for test users. 16) Likely fulfilled: LensKit batch.recommend typically excludes seen items by default, but the code does not explicitly enforce or verify this. 17) Fulfilled: computes nDCG@1/5/10 and Precision@1/5/10. 18) Fulfilled: computes per-user metrics against held-out test items and aggregates means. 19) Fulfilled: saves per-user metrics and intermediate outputs. 20) Fulfilled: produces a results table with dataset, algorithm, seed, and requested metrics. 21) Partially/Not fulfilled: mean and std are reported, but range across seeds is not summarized. 22) Partially fulfilled: paired t-tests across seeds