[2026/05/08 11:37:24] [DEBUG] isgsa.llm: compile_prompt_to_md input: type=<class 'dict'>
[2026/05/08 11:37:24] [DEBUG] isgsa.llm: prompt content: {'Introduction': 'You are an expert recommender systems researcher conducting a code review. Your task is to evaluate whether the code execution was successful or contains bugs. Focus on identifying execution failures, errors, or other issues that would prevent the code from working properly.', 'Research Task': " You are an expert recommender systems research assistant who is looking to help the user with their requests.\nThe user has some idea and you want to conduct creative experiments to gain scientific insights.\nYour aim is to run experiments to gather sufficient results to report back to the user.\nThe idea is:\n\nI'd like to run an experiment to quantify how much data split random seeds affect recommender system accuracy. Please use LensKit 0.14.4 to test three algorithms: ALS, ItemKNN, and Pop. Run this on the following three datasets with implicit feedback: MovieLens100K, Amazon Video Games, Last.FM. The raw files are stored in your working directory with the filenames u.data, VideoGames.csv, UserTaggedArtists-timestamps.dat. First, preprocess all datasets with 5-core filtering. For the Amazon and MovieLens datasets, please also convert any ratings greater than 3 to implicit interactions. Here's the main experimental procedure: Generate 5 different random seeds for data splitting. For each algorithm, dataset, and seed, please do a user-based 80/20 holdout split. Train all models using standard hyperparameters. For the analysis, I need you to measure nDCG@k and Precision@k for k=1, 5, 10 and conduct a short statistical analysis.", 'Implementation': "```python\nimport os\nworking_dir = os.path.join(os.getcwd(), 'working')\nos.makedirs(working_dir, exist_ok=True)\n\nimport warnings\nwarnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n\nimport inspect\nimport numpy as np\nimport pandas as pd\nfrom scipy.stats import ttest_rel, t\n\nfrom lenskit import batch\nfrom lenskit.algorithms import Recommender\nfrom lenskit.algorithms.basic import Popular\nfrom lenskit.algorithms.als import ImplicitMF\nfrom lenskit.algorithms.item_knn import ItemItem\n\nSEEDS = [1, 7, 21, 42, 84]\nKS = [1, 5, 10]\nTOPN = max(KS)\nALS_FEATURES = 50\n\nexperiment_data = {\n    'ml100k': {'metrics': {'train': [], 'val': []}, 'losses': {'train': [], 'val': []}, 'predictions': [], 'ground_truth': [], 'preprocess': []},\n    'amazon_videogames': {'metrics': {'train': [], 'val': []}, 'losses': {'train': [], 'val': []}, 'predictions': [], 'ground_truth': [], 'preprocess': []},\n    'lastfm': {'metrics': {'train': [], 'val': []}, 'losses': {'train': [], 'val': []}, 'predictions': [], 'ground_truth': [], 'preprocess': []},\n}\n\n\ndef robust_read_csv(path, **kwargs):\n    kwargs = dict(kwargs)\n    kwargs.setdefault('on_bad_lines', 'skip')\n    try:\n        return pd.read_csv(path, **kwargs)\n    except TypeError:\n        kwargs.pop('on_bad_lines', None)\n        return pd.read_csv(path, error_bad_lines=False, warn_bad_lines=False, **kwargs)\n\n\ndef standardize_pairs(df, user_col, item_col):\n    out = df[[user_col, item_col]].copy()\n    out.columns = ['user', 'item']\n    out['user'] = out['user'].astype(str).str.strip()\n    out['item'] = out['item'].astype(str).str.strip()\n    out = out.replace({'': np.nan, 'nan': np.nan, 'None': np.nan})\n    out = out.dropna().drop_duplicates().reset_index(drop=True)\n    return out\n\n\ndef k_core_filter(df, user_col='user', item_col='item', min_uc=5, min_ic=5):\n    cur = df[[user_col, item_col]].drop_duplicates().copy()\n    while True:\n        uc = cur[user_col].value_counts()\n        ic = cur[item_col].value_counts()\n        keep_u = set(uc[uc >= min_uc].index)\n        keep_i = set(ic[ic >= min_ic].index)\n        new = cur[cur[user_col].isin(keep_u) & cur[item_col].isin(keep_i)].copy()\n        if len(new) == len(cur):\n            break\n        cur = new\n    return cur.reset_index(drop=True)\n\n\ndef load_ml100k(path='u.data'):\n    raw = robust_read_csv(path, sep='\\t', header=None, names=['user', 'item', 'rating', 'timestamp'])\n    raw['rating'] = pd.to_numeric(raw['rating'], errors='coerce')\n    raw = raw.dropna(subset=['user', 'item', 'rating'])\n    pre_n = len(raw)\n    raw = raw[raw['rating'] > 3]\n    pairs = standardize_pairs(raw, 'user', 'item')\n    filtered = k_core_filter(pairs)\n    summary = {\n        'raw_rows': int(pre_n), 'after_threshold': int(len(pairs)), 'after_kcore': int(len(filtered)),\n        'users': int(filtered.user.nunique()), 'items': int(filtered.item.nunique()), 'dropped_rows': int(pre_n - len(filtered))\n    }\n    return filtered, summary\n\n\ndef load_amazon(path='VideoGames.csv'):\n    raw = robust_read_csv(path, header=None)\n    if raw.shape[1] < 3:\n        raise ValueError('VideoGames.csv must have at least 3 columns')\n    raw = raw.iloc[:, :4].copy()\n    raw.columns = ['user', 'item', 'rating', 'timestamp'][:raw.shape[1]]\n    raw['rating'] = pd.to_numeric(raw['rating'], errors='coerce')\n    raw = raw.dropna(subset=['user', 'item', 'rating'])\n    pre_n = len(raw)\n    raw = raw[raw['rating'] > 3]\n    pairs = standardize_pairs(raw, 'user', 'item')\n    filtered = k_core_filter(pairs)\n    summary = {\n        'raw_rows': int(pre_n), 'after_threshold': int(len(pairs)), 'after_kcore': int(len(filtered)),\n        'users': int(filtered.user.nunique()), 'items': int(filtered.item.nunique()), 'dropped_rows': int(pre_n - len(filtered))\n    }\n    return filtered, summary\n\n\ndef load_lastfm(path='UserTaggedArtists-timestamps.dat'):\n    raw = robust_read_csv(path, sep='\\t')\n    cols = {c.lower(): c for c in raw.columns}\n    user_col = cols['userid'] if 'userid' in cols else raw.columns[0]\n    item_col = cols['artistid'] if 'artistid' in cols else raw.columns[1]\n    raw = raw.dropna(subset=[user_col, item_col])\n    pre_n = len(raw)\n    pairs = standardize_pairs(raw, user_col, item_col)\n    filtered = k_core_filter(pairs)\n    summary = {\n        'raw_rows': int(pre_n), 'after_threshold': int(len(pairs)), 'after_kcore': int(len(filtered)),\n        'users': int(filtered.user.nunique()), 'items': int(filtered.item.nunique()), 'dropped_rows': int(pre_n - len(filtered))\n    }\n    return filtered, summary\n\n\ndef user_holdout_split(df, test_ratio=0.2, seed=42):\n    rng = np.random.default_rng(seed)\n    user_sizes = df.groupby('user').size()\n    valid_users = user_sizes[user_sizes >= 2].index\n    excluded_users = int((user_sizes < 2).sum())\n    df = df[df['user'].isin(valid_users)].copy()\n    train_parts, test_parts = [], []\n    for _, g in df.groupby('user', sort=False):\n        n = len(g)\n        n_test = max(1, int(np.floor(n * test_ratio)))\n        if n_test >= n:\n            n_test = n - 1\n        idx = np.arange(n)\n        rng.shuffle(idx)\n        mask = np.zeros(n, dtype=bool)\n        mask[idx[:n_test]] = True\n        train_parts.append(g.iloc[~mask])\n        test_parts.append(g.iloc[mask])\n    train = pd.concat(train_parts, ignore_index=True)\n    test = pd.concat(test_parts, ignore_index=True)\n    return train, test, excluded_users\n\n\ndef make_algo(name, seed):\n    if name == 'Pop':\n        return Recommender.adapt(Popular())\n    if name == 'ALS':\n        params = inspect.signature(ImplicitMF).parameters\n        kwargs = {}\n        if 'features' in params:\n            kwargs['features'] = ALS_FEATURES\n        if 'iterations' in params:\n            kwargs['iterations'] = 20\n        if 'weight' in params:\n            kwargs['weight'] = 40\n        if 'method' in params:\n            kwargs['method'] = 'cg'\n        if 'use_ratings' in params:\n            kwargs['use_ratings'] = False\n        if 'progress' in params:\n            kwargs['progress'] = False\n        if 'rng_spec' in params:\n            kwargs['rng_spec'] = seed\n        elif 'random_state' in params:\n            kwargs['random_state'] = seed\n        return Recommender.adapt(ImplicitMF(**kwargs))\n    if name == 'ItemKNN':\n        params = inspect.signature(ItemItem).parameters\n        kwargs = {}\n        if 'nnbrs' in params:\n            kwargs['nnbrs'] = 20\n        if 'min_nbrs' in params:\n            kwargs['min_nbrs'] = 1\n        if 'min_sim' in params:\n            kwargs['min_sim'] = 1.0e-6\n        if 'save_nbrs' in params:\n            kwargs['save_nbrs'] = 100\n        if 'center' in params:\n            kwargs['center'] = False\n        if 'aggregate' in params:\n            kwargs['aggregate'] = 'sum'\n        return Recommender.adapt(ItemItem(**kwargs))\n    raise ValueError(name)\n\n\ndef precision_at_k(recs, truth, k):\n    if k <= 0:\n        return 0.0\n    recs = recs[:k]\n    return float(sum(1 for x in recs if x in truth) / k)\n\n\ndef ndcg_at_k(recs, truth, k):\n    recs = recs[:k]\n    dcg = sum((1.0 / np.log2(i + 2)) for i, x in enumerate(recs) if x in truth)\n    ideal = min(len(truth), k)\n    if ideal == 0:\n        return 0.0\n    idcg = sum(1.0 / np.log2(i + 2) for i in range(ideal))\n    return float(dcg / idcg)\n\n\ndef evaluate_model(model, train, test, algo_name, dataset_name, seed):\n    model.fit(train)\n    users = np.array(sorted(test['user'].unique()))\n    truth = test.groupby('user')['item'].apply(set).to_dict()\n    recs = batch.recommend(model, users, TOPN)\n    if recs is None or len(recs) == 0:\n        recs = pd.DataFrame(columns=['user', 'item', 'rank', 'score'])\n    recs = recs[['user', 'item']].copy() if len(recs) else pd.DataFrame(columns=['user', 'item'])\n    user_recs = recs.groupby('user')['item'].apply(list).to_dict() if len(recs) else {}\n\n    rows = []\n    for u in users:\n        r = user_recs.get(u, [])\n        tset = truth.get(u, set())\n        row = {'dataset': dataset_name, 'algorithm': algo_name, 'seed': seed, 'user': u}\n        for k in KS:\n            row[f'P@{k}'] = precision_at_k(r, tset, k)\n            row[f'nDCG@{k}'] = ndcg_at_k(r, tset, k)\n        rows.append(row)\n    udf = pd.DataFrame(rows)\n    summary = {'dataset': dataset_name, 'algorithm': algo_name, 'seed': seed}\n    for c in [f'P@{k}' for k in KS] + [f'nDCG@{k}' for k in KS]:\n        summary[c] = float(udf[c].mean())\n    val_loss = 1.0 - summary['nDCG@10']\n    print(f'Epoch {seed}: validation_loss = {val_loss:.4f} | {dataset_name} | {algo_name}')\n    print({k: round(v, 4) for k, v in summary.items() if k not in ['dataset', 'algorithm', 'seed']})\n\n    experiment_data[dataset_name]['metrics']['val'].append({'timestamp_seed': seed, **summary})\n    experiment_data[dataset_name]['losses']['val'].append({'timestamp_seed': seed, 'algorithm': algo_name, 'validation_loss': val_loss})\n    experiment_data[dataset_name]['predictions'].append({'seed': seed, 'algorithm': algo_name, 'rows': recs.to_dict('records')})\n    experiment_data[dataset_name]['ground_truth'].append({'seed': seed, 'algorithm': algo_name, 'rows': test[['user', 'item']].to_dict('records')})\n    return udf, summary\n\n\ndatasets = {}\nloaders = {\n    'ml100k': load_ml100k,\n    'amazon_videogames': load_amazon,\n    'lastfm': load_lastfm,\n}\nfiles = {\n    'ml100k': 'u.data',\n    'amazon_videogames': 'VideoGames.csv',\n    'lastfm': 'UserTaggedArtists-timestamps.dat',\n}\n\nfor dname in ['ml100k', 'amazon_videogames', 'lastfm']:\n    df, summary = loaders[dname](files[dname])\n    datasets[dname] = df\n    experiment_data[dname]['preprocess'].append(summary)\n    print(f'Loaded {dname}: {summary}')\n\nall_user_metrics, all_seed_metrics, preprocess_rows = [], [], []\nfor dname, df in datasets.items():\n    preprocess_rows.append({'dataset': dname, **experiment_data[dname]['preprocess'][0]})\n    for seed in SEEDS:\n        train, test, excluded_users = user_holdout_split(df, test_ratio=0.2, seed=seed)\n        split_info = {'timestamp_seed': seed, 'n_train': int(len(train)), 'n_test': int(len(test)), 'excluded_users_lt2': int(excluded_users)}\n        experiment_data[dname]['metrics']['train'].append(split_info)\n        print(f'Split {dname} seed={seed}: train={len(train)}, test={len(test)}, excluded_users_lt2={excluded_users}')\n        for aname in ['ALS', 'ItemKNN', 'Pop']:\n            algo = make_algo(aname, seed)\n            udf, summary = evaluate_model(algo, train, test, aname, dname, seed)\n            all_user_metrics.append(udf)\n            all_seed_metrics.append(summary)\n\nuser_metrics_df = pd.concat(all_user_metrics, ignore_index=True)\nseed_metrics_df = pd.DataFrame(all_seed_metrics)\npreprocess_df = pd.DataFrame(preprocess_rows)\n\nprint('\\nAggregate results over seeds (mean/std/min/max):')\nagg = seed_metrics_df.groupby(['dataset', 'algorithm'])[[f'P@{k}' for k in KS] + [f'nDCG@{k}' for k in KS]].agg(['mean', 'std', 'min', 'max'])\nprint(agg.round(4))\n\nprint('\\nSeed sensitivity summary (std across seeds):')\nseed_var_df = seed_metrics_df.groupby(['dataset', 'algorithm'])[[f'P@{k}' for k in KS] + [f'nDCG@{k}' for k in KS]].std().reset_index()\nprint(seed_var_df.round(4))\n\nprint('\\nPaired t-tests and 95% CI for nDCG@10 differences across seeds:')\nstats_rows = []\nfor dname in datasets:\n    sub = seed_metrics_df[seed_metrics_df['dataset'] == dname]\n    for a1, a2 in [('ALS', 'Pop'), ('ItemKNN', 'Pop'), ('ALS', 'ItemKNN')]:\n        x = sub[sub['algorithm'] == a1].sort_values('seed')['nDCG@10'].values\n        y = sub[sub['algorithm'] == a2].sort_values('seed')['nDCG@10'].values\n        if len(x) == len(y) == len(SEEDS):\n            diff = x - y\n            mean_diff = float(diff.mean())\n            sd = float(diff.std(ddof=1)) if len(diff) > 1 else 0.0\n            se = sd / np.sqrt(len(diff)) if len(diff) > 1 else 0.0\n            crit = t.ppf(0.975, df=len(diff) - 1) if len(diff) > 1 else np.nan\n            ci_low = mean_diff - crit * se if len(diff) > 1 else np.nan\n            ci_high = mean_diff + crit * se if len(diff) > 1 else np.nan\n            tt, pv = ttest_rel(x, y)\n            row = {\n                'dataset': dname,\n                'compare': f'{a1} - {a2}',\n                'mean_diff_nDCG@10': mean_diff,\n                'std_diff_nDCG@10': sd,\n                't_stat': float(tt),\n                'p_value': float(pv),\n                'ci95_low': float(ci_low),\n                'ci95_high': float(ci_high)\n            }\n            stats_rows.append(row)\n            print(row)\nstats_df = pd.DataFrame(stats_rows)\n\nnp.save(os.path.join(working_dir, 'experiment_data.npy'), experiment_data, allow_pickle=True)\nnp.save(os.path.join(working_dir, 'preprocess_summary.npy'), preprocess_df.to_dict('records'), allow_pickle=True)\nnp.save(os.path.join(working_dir, 'seed_metrics_array.npy'), seed_metrics_df.to_dict('records'), allow_pickle=True)\nnp.save(os.path.join(working_dir, 'user_metrics_array.npy'), user_metrics_df.to_dict('records'), allow_pickle=True)\nnp.save(os.path.join(working_dir, 'seed_sensitivity_array.npy'), seed_var_df.to_dict('records'), allow_pickle=True)\nnp.save(os.path.join(working_dir, 'stats_summary_array.npy'), stats_df.to_dict('records'), allow_pickle=True)\nnp.savez_compressed(\n    os.path.join(working_dir, 'results_tables.npz'),\n    seed_metrics=seed_metrics_df.to_records(index=False),\n    user_metrics=user_metrics_df.to_records(index=False),\n    preprocess=preprocess_df.to_records(index=False),\n    seed_sensitivity=seed_var_df.to_records(index=False),\n    stats=stats_df.to_records(index=False)\n)\n\npreprocess_df.to_csv(os.path.join(working_dir, 'preprocess_summary.csv'), index=False)\nseed_metrics_df.to_csv(os.path.join(working_dir, 'seed_metrics.csv'), index=False)\nuser_metrics_df.to_csv(os.path.join(working_dir, 'user_metrics.csv'), index=False)\nseed_var_df.to_csv(os.path.join(working_dir, 'seed_sensitivity.csv'), index=False)\nstats_df.to_csv(os.path.join(working_dir, 'stats_summary.csv'), index=False)\nprint(f'Artifacts saved to: {working_dir}')\n```", 'Execution Output': '```\nLoaded ml100k: {\'raw_rows\': 100000, \'after_threshold\': 55375, \'after_kcore\': 54413, \'users